M.G.L. c. 231, \u00a7 2.proposition: This Court has jurisdiction over this matter pursuant to M.G.L. c. 231, § 2 and the breach of the covenant of quiet enjoyment in M.G.L. c. 186, § 14.

M.G.L. c. 186, \u00a7 14.proposition: Pursuant to M.G.L. c. 186, § 14, "any lessor or landlord who directly or indirectly interferes with the quiet enjoyment of any residential premises by the occupant" shall be liable to the tenant for actual damages or three months' rent, whichever is greater, and the costs of the action, including attorney's fees.
